The Chronicle Nduduzo Tshuma THE Minister of Transport and Infrastructure Development, Biggie Joel Matiza, has died. He was 59. The Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services, Mr Nick Mangwana, confirmed Minster Matiza’s death on Friday evening. Minister Matiza was also the Zanu-PF Mashonaland East provincial chairperson and the party’s legislator for Murewa South. More details to follow….